The paper deals with assessing the integrity of multimedia packages containing images and captions using computer vision and natural language processing methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves natural language processing, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper deals with multimedia data, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Since the paper deals with detecting manipulations, it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
